<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="191" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,775,778,1025]" lastBlockId="4.[835,1474,194,251]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,272,778,802]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Diagnosis. –</emphasis>
The arrangement of cheliceral teeth of the new species is similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Peckham &amp; Peckham, 1907" authorityName="Peckham &amp; Peckham" authorityYear="1907" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bathippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shelfordii">
<emphasis box="[425,643,811,834]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Bathippus shelfordii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Peckham, G" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" pagination="603 - 653" refId="ref5608" refString="Peckham, G. W. &amp; E. G. Peckham, 1907. The Attidae of Borneo. Transactions of the Wisconsin Academy of Sciences, Arts and Letters, 15: 603 - 653." type="journal article" year="1907">Peckham &amp; Peckham, 1907</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Peckham, G" box="[320,688,842,865]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" pagination="603 - 653" refId="ref5608" refString="Peckham, G. W. &amp; E. G. Peckham, 1907. The Attidae of Borneo. Transactions of the Wisconsin Academy of Sciences, Arts and Letters, 15: 603 - 653." type="journal article" year="1907">Peckham &amp; Peckham, 1907: 620</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Zabka, M" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" pagination="421 - 479" refId="ref6120" refString="Zabka, M., 1988. Salticidae (Araneae) of Oriental, Australian and Pacific regions, III. Annales Zoologici Warszawa, 41: 421 - 479." type="journal article" year="1988">Zabka, 1988: 431</bibRefCitation>
, f. 22-28), but differs from the latter in the structure of palpal organ; the palpal organ of the new species resembles that of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thorell, 1881)" baseAuthorityName="Thorell" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[224,642,938,962]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bathippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="molossus">
<emphasis box="[224,453,939,962]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Bathippus molossus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thorell, T" box="[473,634,938,961]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" pagination="1 - 720" refId="ref5957" refString="Thorell, T., 1881. Studi sui Ragni Malesi e Papuanti. III. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 17: 1 - 720." type="journal article" year="1881">Thorell, 1881</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Thorell, 1881: 553" authorityName="Thorell" authorityPageNumber="553" authorityYear="1881" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Plexippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="molossus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Plexippus molossus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thorell, T" box="[246,460,970,993]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" pagination="1 - 720" refId="ref5957" refString="Thorell, T., 1881. Studi sui Ragni Malesi e Papuanti. III. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 17: 1 - 720." type="journal article" year="1881">Thorell, 1881: 553</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 708; 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thorell" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[534,755,971,994]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Bathippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="molossus">
<emphasis box="[534,755,971,994]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Bathippus molossus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- Prószynski théfrom, 1984: 8), but differs the latter in embolus relatively longer, coiled in more than one circle and tibial apophysis not hook-like.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="191" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[835,1475,295,1024]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,1076,295,319]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[835,996,295,319]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Description. –</emphasis>
Males
</emphasis>
. Total length 6.75 (
<typeStatus box="[1306,1407,295,318]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">paratype</typeStatus>
)-8.45. Length of 
<typeStatus box="[942,1035,329,352]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">holotype</typeStatus>
8.45: cephalothorax 3.42 long, 2.79 wide; abdomen 5.09 long, 2.03 wide. Carapace (
<figureCitation box="[1318,1408,362,385]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[136,172,2065,2086]" captionTargetBox="[201,1402,1097,2000]" captionTargetId="figure-412@4.[187,1424,1084,2005]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Bathippus rectus, new species, holotype (ZRC.ARA.52). A. male; B. left chelicera, ventral view; C. left palp, ventral view; D. same, lateral view. Scales: A, B = 1.0 mm, C, D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618804/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
) dark brown, the PME and PLE surrounded by black circle. Eye sizes: AME 0.87, ALE 0.49, PME 0.09, PLE 0.46. Anterior eye row 2.48 wide, posterior row 2.25 wide, eye area 1.62 long. Chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1125,497,520]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[136,172,2065,2086]" captionTargetBox="[201,1402,1097,2000]" captionTargetId="figure-412@4.[187,1424,1084,2005]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Bathippus rectus, new species, holotype (ZRC.ARA.52). A. male; B. left chelicera, ventral view; C. left palp, ventral view; D. same, lateral view. Scales: A, B = 1.0 mm, C, D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618804/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
) long, orange yellow, with 3 promarginal teeth and 1 retromarginal tooth. Endite and labium orange yellow, sternum yellow. Legs: femora I, II and patellae I, II dark red, other segments orange yellow. Femur I dorsally and patella I dorsally and ventrally with dense scopulae. Tibiae I, II and metatarsi I, II each with 4 pairs of ventral spines. Leg measurements: I 13.28 (3.87+5.22+ 3.06+1.13); II 10.36 (3.20+3.69+2.34+1.13); I I I 1 5. 0 4 (5. 0 9 + 4. 9 1 + 4. 1 4 + 0. 9 0); I V 1 0. 0 9 (2.93+3.15+3.20+0.81). Leg formula: 3124. Dorsum of abdomen grayish brown (yellow in 
<typeStatus box="[1212,1309,833,856]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">paratype</typeStatus>
), centrally with 2 pairs of small brown spots; venter grayish brown, with 4 rows of light yellow, longitudinal markings. Embolus of palpal organ (
<figureCitation box="[990,1122,933,956]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[136,172,2065,2086]" captionTargetBox="[201,1402,1097,2000]" captionTargetId="figure-412@4.[187,1424,1084,2005]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Bathippus rectus, new species, holotype (ZRC.ARA.52). A. male; B. left chelicera, ventral view; C. left palp, ventral view; D. same, lateral view. Scales: A, B = 1.0 mm, C, D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618804/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Figs. 4C, D</figureCitation>
) slender, coiled into more than one circle, its basal part swollen as a bulb; tibial apophysis finger-like, not curved.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
